// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/preprocess/p08/fail.test — P8 search-path failure: an
// `#include` whose target file is not findable in any configured
// search root raises a generic "could not find include" diagnostic.
//
// Per the contract row in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/preprocessor-seam.contract.md`:
//   "search-path failure raises generic 'could not find include'"
//
// This diagnostic string is **NOT** in the FR-037 locked-string
// table — `diagnostic-output.contract.md`'s "Mandatory diagnostic-
// string fixtures" only locks P3, P6, P7, P9, and lex-unterminated.
// We assert the SHAPE (`error: ...could not find...include...` per
// SC-004 regex) but not the precise message text — leaving the
// implementer freedom to tune wording without a contract amendment.
//
// **RED state**: against the unchanged Phase-3 tree the lexer
// tokenizes `#include "missing.nsl"` literally. Phase-4's
// `IncludeSearchPath` resolves the lookup; on failure it raises the
// diagnostic.

// RUN: echo '#include "this_file_does_not_exist.nsl"' > %t.nsl
// RUN: not %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

// SC-004 regex shape (path:line:col: error: ...) without locking the
// message text:
// CHECK: error: {{.*}}could not find{{.*}}include
